In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June 2014 as National Caribbean-American Heritage Month. He highlights the contributions of Caribbean Americans to various aspects of American society, including science, medicine, business, and the arts. The President emphasizes the importance of friendship and cooperation with Caribbean neighbors and announces plans to promote social justice, prosperity, and educational opportunities in the Caribbean. He also mentions the desire to advance immigration reform to allow future generations of Caribbean Americans to contribute their talents to the United States. The President calls on all Americans to celebrate the history and culture of Caribbean Americans through appropriate ceremonies and activities.